Sojitz Corp. and Marubeni Corp. are
among investors that will spend A$200 million ($201 million) to
double production capacity at the Lake Vermont coal mine in
Australia.  The companies, including Jellinbah Group and American
Metals & Coal International Inc., plan to boost capacity to 8
million metric tons a year by 2013, according to a statement
